comment.body: In the clearnet I know two Git hosting services.The centralized Github and the decentralized Gitlab.I like the idea of a decentralized service but I like Github more because I can search one search index with everything and don't have to search at dozens of different instances.You did it right!It's even more decentralized than Gitlab but there is only one repository index where I can see all repositories.That's the best Git hosting solution which I know!

I've been using Bitcoins since they were worth $400.
Some days ago they were worth more than $7000.
Now they lost a part of their worth and I used the great opportunity to get a part of a Bitcoin some dollars cheaper and earn while they get more expensive again.
I'm sure that they will get more expensive again.
Some people are pissed because the SegWit2x hardfork didn't happen but I'm sure that things will get normal soon.
Most users are investors who don't care about any technical changes.
